  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "Amid escalating US-Iran hostilities in the ongoing 2026 conflict—sparked by US and Israeli strikes on February 28—traders focus on today's 60-day War Powers Resolution deadline, requiring President Trump to notify Congress or end military actions like the naval blockade squeezing Iran's oil exports. No formal congressional declaration of war has occurred, as the Constitution reserves that power for lawmakers, who last used it in World War II; modern engagements typically rely on Authorizations for Use of Military Force (AUMF). A fragile April 7 ceasefire mediated by Pakistan has stalled amid Iranian strikes damaging over a dozen US bases and Trump's signals of potential new airstrikes, with Speaker Johnson insisting the US is \"not at war.\" Upcoming congressional votes on war powers or AUMF could clarify, but outright declaration remains improbable given historical precedent.",
    "context_requires_regen": true,
    "context_updated_at": "2026-05-01T08:46:58.030Z"
  }
